The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Former scribe passes away
                                                   Former scribe passes away
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Former national basketball player and sports journalist Javed Akhtar died in Mumbai on Wednesday. He was 58 and is survived by wife Nayanthara and three sons.         
	Akhtar, who covered major events like the cricket World Cup and the Asian Games, passed away due to a malignant stomach tumor, family sources said.         
	The soft-spoken Akhtar took ill 10 days ago and the end came around 3 pm.         
	During the early years of The Telegraph, he contributed articles and photographs. Akhtar held a senior position in the public relations firm that handled the Indian Premier League last year.         
	After starting his career in Mumbai, he spent a few years in the Gulf. He was also the media manager of the Pak cricket team that visited India in 2007.                                                                                                                       
